      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a museum-quality example of the pinnacle of 90s Japanese engineering. Powered by the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine, the vacuum lines and 'rat's nest' have been meticulously maintained to ensure a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 units. Compression testing yields optimal, consistent results across all rotor faces, reflecting a healthy apex seal state. The 5-speed manual transmission is paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, providing exceptional power delivery. The chassis remains corner-balanced and true, featuring its original lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension components and four-piston braking system. With no evidence of heat-cycling fatigue on the cooling system or oxidation on the underbody, this FD is a rare find for the discerning purist seeking an unmolested, analog driving experience.",
      "price": 49200.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 37
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Low mileage. Clean title. No accidents. Full service history. Inspections welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
